    "code": "012", 
    "data": "You may then walk to the mosque with tranquility and solemnity. While leaving your house towards the mosque, you may say the following:\nبِسْمِ اللهِ الَّذِيْ خَلَقَنِيْ فَہُوَيَہْدِيْنِيْ\nBISMIL LAAHIL LAZEE KHALAQANEE FAHOWA YAHDEENEE\nIn the Name of Allah Who created me, then He has shown me the way,\nوَ الَّذِيْ ہُوَيُطْعِمُنِيْ وَيَسْقِيْنِيْ\nWAL LAZEE HOWA YUT-E’MONEE WA YASQEENEE\nWho gives me to eat and gives me to drink,\nوَ اِذَا مَرِضْتُ فَہُوَيَشْفِيْنِيْ\nWA EZAA MARIZTO FAHOWA YASHFEENEE\nwhen I am sick, then He restores me to health,\nوَ الَّذِيْ يُمِيْـتُـنِيْ ثُمَّ يُحْيِيْنِيْ\nWAL LAZEE YOMEETONEE SUMMA YOHYEENEE\nWho will cause me to die, then give me life,\nوَ الَّذِيْٓ اَطْمَــعُ اَنْ يَّغْفِرَ لِيْ خَطِيْۗــــــَٔــتِيْ يَوْمَ الدِّيْنِ\nWAL LAZEE ATMA-O’ ANY YAGHFERA LEE KHATEEE-ATEE YAWMAD DEENE\nand Who, I hope, will forgive me my mistakes on the day of judgment.\nرَبِّ ہَبْ لِيْ حُكْمًا وَّاَلْـحِقْنِيْ بِالصّٰلِحِيْنَ\nRABBE HAB LEE  HUKMANW  WA ALHIQNEE BIS-SAALEHEEN\nMy Lord, (please) grant me wisdom, join me with the righteous ones,\nوَ اجْعَلْ لِّيْ لِسَانَ صِدْقٍ فِي الْاٰخِرِيْنَ\nWAJ A’L LEE LESAANA SIDQIN FIL AAKHEREENA\nordain for me a goodly mention among posterity,\nوَ اجْعَلْنِيْ مِنْ وَّرَثَۃِ جَنَّۃِ النَّعِيْمِ\nWAJ A’LNEE MINW WARASATE JANNATIN NA-E’EME\nmake me of the heirs of the garden of bliss,\nوَ اغْفِرْ لِاَبِيْٓ\nWAGH FIR LE-ABEE.\nand forgive my father.\nBefore you enter the mosque, you may check the bottom of your shoes, lest there may be an impure thing sticking to them.\nYou may then enter, by preceding your right foot to the left, and say the following:\nبِسْمِ اللهِ وَبِاللهِ\nBISMIL LAAHE WA BILLAAHE\nIn the Name of Allah (I begin), in Allah (I trust),\nوَمِنَ اللهِ وَاِلٰى اللهِ\nWA MENAL LAAHE WA ELAL LAAHE\nfrom Allah (I derive power), to Allah (I refer all my affairs),\nوَخَيْرُ الْاَسْمَاءِ كُلِّهَا لِلهِ\nWA KHAYRUL ASMAA-E KULLEHAA LILLAAHE\nand the most excellent of all names are Allah’s.\nتَوَكَّلْتُ عَلٰى اللهِ\nTAWAKKALTO A’LAL LAAHE\nI put my trust in Allah.\nوَ لَا حَوْلَ وَ لَا قُوَّةَ اِلَّا بِاللهِ\nWA LAA HAWLA WA LAA QUWWATA ILLAA BILLAAHE\nThere is neither might nor power except with Allah.\nاَللّٰهُمَّ صَلِّ عَلٰى مُحَمَّدٍ وَ آلِ مُحَمَّدٍ\nALLAHUMMA SALLE A’LAA MOHAMMADIN WA AALE MOHAMMADIN\nO Allah, (please) send blessings upon Muhammad and the Household of Muhammad,\nوَ افْتَحْ لِيْ اَبْوَابَ رَحْمَتِكَ وَ تَوْبَتِكَ\nWAF TAH LEE ABWABA RAHMATEKA WA TAWBATEKA\nopen before me the doors to Your mercy and admission of repentance,\nوَ اَغْلِقْ عَنِّيْ اَبْوَابَ مَعْصِيَتِكَ\nWA AGHLIQ A’NNEE ABWABA MA’SEYATEKA\nclose in my face the doors to the acts of disobedience to You,\nوَ اجْعَلْنِيْ مِنْ زُوَّارِكَ\nWAJ A’LNEE MIN ZUWWAAREKA\nmake me of Your frequent visitors,\nوَ عُمَّارِ مَسَاجِدِكَ\nWA U’MMAARE MASAAJEDEKA\nconstructors of Your mosques,\nوَ مِمَّنْ يُنَاجِيْكَ فِيْ اللَّيْلِ وَ النَّهَارِ\nWA MIMMAN YONAAJEEKA FIL LAYLE WAN NAHAARE\nthose who talk to You confidentially at nights and on days,\nوَ مِنَ الَّذِيْنَ هُمْ فِي صَلَاتِهِمْ خَاشِعُوْنَ\nWA MENAL LAZEENA HUM FEE SALAATEHIM KHAASHEO’ONA\nand those who are submissive in their prayers,\nوَ ادْحَرْ عَنِّي الشَّيْطَانَ الرَّجِيْمَ\nWAD HAR A’NNISH SHAYTAANAR RAJEEMA\nand fend off from me the accursed Satan\nوَ جُنُوْدَ اِبْلِيسَ اَجْمَعِيْنَ\nWA JONOODA IBLEESA AJMAE’ENA\nand all troops of Iblees.", 
    "title": "Etiquettes of attending Mosques"
}